# ✅ Architecture (Understand This First)

    Auth / Session Cookie → HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax
    CSRF Token            → Normal cookie (readable by JS)
    React                 → Reads CSRF cookie, sends it as header
    Server                → Validates cookie + header match

### Why this is secure

*   ✅ Attacker site **cannot read cookies**
*   ✅ Attacker site **cannot add custom headers**
*   ✅ Browser still sends cookies → CSRF blocked

